President Biden has declared a major disaster in California due to severe winter storms, winds, flooding, landslides, and mudslides that began on February 21, 2023. This declaration allows for federal aid to supplement state, tribal, and local recovery efforts. Affected individuals in seven counties can receive assistance, including grants for temporary housing and home repairs, low-cost loans for uninsured property losses, and other programs. Federal funding is also available for emergency work, facility repair or replacement, and hazard mitigation measures. Andrew F. Grant of FEMA has been appointed to coordinate federal recovery operations. Damage assessments are ongoing, and additional counties may be designated for assistance. For more information, contact the FEMA News Desk.